    <fr:title text="Space of Continuous Functions">Space of Continuous Functions</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-0006.tree</fr:source-path>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The space of continuous functions on an interval <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[a,b]]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C([a,b])]]></fr:tex>, consists of all continuous real-valued or complex-valued functions defined on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[a,b]]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>This space is typically equipped with the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000E.xml" addr="FA-000E" title="Sup norm">sup norm</fr:link>, which makes it a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000F.xml" addr="FA-000F" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
