            <fr:title text="Banach Space">Banach Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-000F.tree</fr:source-path>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A Banach space is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000N.xml" addr="FA-000N" title="Complete">complete</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0017.xml" addr="FA-0017" title="Normed vector space">normed vector space</fr:link>. That is, a Banach space is a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> with a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0018.xml" addr="FA-0018" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||\cdot ||]]></fr:tex> such that every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000X.xml" addr="FA-000X" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> (with respect to the metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(u, v) = ||u - v||]]></fr:tex>) converges to a vector in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Banach spaces are fundamental in functional analysis and named after Stefan Banach. They provide the right setting for many important results in analysis, including the Hahn-Banach theorem, the open mapping theorem, and the closed graph theorem.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Examples include the spaces <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \geq  1]]></fr:tex>, the space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C([a,b])]]></fr:tex> of continuous functions on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[a,b]]]></fr:tex> with the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000E.xml" addr="FA-000E" title="Sup norm">sup norm</fr:link>, and all finite-dimensional normed vector spaces.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
